<dl id="n42148e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42148e">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42148e"> 148(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> fortitudinous / ajax&apos;s rowdinoisey / tenementa <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n42148e"><li>FW 53.16 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n42148e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n42148e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n42148e">MS BL 47475-24</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:291 <a name="cd8" href="../../ff/fdra/cda.htm#cd8">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/cd8.htm#n42148e">Draft: I.3&sect;1.8</a>/2.8/3.8 </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n33022c" href="n33all.htm#n33022c">N33 (VI.B.4):022(c)</a> and <a name="n52178g" href="n52all.htm#n52178g">N52 (VI.B.42):178(g)</a>. According to a tradition (which has been disputed: see <cite>Notes and Queries</cite>, <a href=" https://books.google.ie/books?id=YC217MX35oIC&pg=PA461&dq=fortitudo+eius+rhodum+tenuit&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwickq2Plq7pAhUxTxUIHTBmDaYQ6AEIZzAH#v=onepage&q=fortitudo%20eius%20rhodum%20tenuit&f=false" target="_blank">4th s. VI Nov. 26, 1870, p. 461</a>) the Knights of the Order of the Hospital of St John of Jerusalem (who had conducted fighting retreats from the Holy Land to Cyprus, and from Cyprus to Rhodes) conferred on Amadeus V, Count of Savoy (1249Â–1323), their cross, with the device F.E.R.T. (<mark><i>Fortitudo Ejus Rhodum Tenuit</i></mark>: his bravery has held Rhodes) following his victory over Saracens at the 1315 siege of Rhodes. </mm> </dd></dl>
